Envelope.mcc/Envelope.mcc

   NAME
	Envelope -- ... (V14)

   FUNCTION
	This class provides you with an easy way to edit
	the kinds of envelopes used by most synthesizers. Attributes
	to allow for editing of most pitch, amplitude and filter 
	envelopes are provided.

	Each knob has a time value (horizontal) and a level value
        (vertical). The range for them both is [0;127]. The top of 
        the gadget is level 0 and the bottom is 127. It's up to you 
        to compensate for this when storing the values of the gadget 
        in your own data structures.


Envelope.mcc/MUIA_Envelope_Text

   NAME
	MUIA_Envelope_Text, (V1) [IS.], Object **

   FUNCTION
	With MUIA_Envelope_Text you can get text readouts of the knob 
	values. The ptr given is a ptr to an array with 4 text gadgets.

Envelope.mcc/MUIA_Envelope_NoL4

   NAME
	MUIA_Envelope_NoL4, (V1) [IS.], BOOL

   FUNCTION
	Locks the level of the last knob making it impossible to edit
	the level for that knob. Normally used for Amplitude-envelopes.

	Defaults to FALSE

Envelope.mcc/MUIA_Envelope_ZeroLine

   NAME
	MUIA_Envelope_ZeroLine, (V1) [IS.], LONG

   FUNCTION
