Envelope.mcc/MUIA_Envelope_StartAtBottom

   NAME
	MUIA_Envelope_StartAtBottom, (V1) [IS.], BOOL

   FUNCTION
	If TRUE makes the start point for the line to 
	knob 0 start at the bottom instead of the middle of the gadget.

	Defaults to FALSE

Envelope.mcc/MUIA_Envelope_EndLine

   NAME
	MUIA_Envelope_EndLine, (V1) [IS.], BOOL

   FUNCTION
	If TRUE this will draw a horizontal line from the last knob all 
	the way to the right side of the gadget

	Defaults to FALSE

Envelope.mcc/MUIA_Envelope_MinLevel

   NAME
	MUIA_Envelope_MinLevel, (V1) [IS.], LONG

   FUNCTION
	Sets the minimium internal level for the all the knobs.
	Can be used to make the levels go from -63 to +63.
        
   SEE ALSO
        the Envelope-Demo source code

Envelope.mcc/MUIA_Envelope_DisplayLevelAdjust

   NAME
	MUIA_Envelope_DisplayLevelAdjust, (V1) [IS.], LONG

   FUNCTION
	The adjust value for displayed levels. The level displayed is
	calculated like this: DisplayValue = (TextAdjust - KnobLevel)

	Defaults to 127. Makes top of the gadget read level 127 and 
	the bottom 0.

